Yes, the problem persists.

Here is the generated C code for the *good* case:

```c
_tmp0_ = gst_parse_bin_from_description_full ("fakesrc name=fake ! identity", TRUE, NULL, GST_PARSE_FLAG_NONE, &_inner_error_);
if (_tmp0_ != NULL) {
	g_object_ref_sink (_tmp0_);
}
source = _tmp0_;
if (G_UNLIKELY (_inner_error_ != NULL)) {
	goto __catch4_g_error;
}
_tmp1_ = gst_bin_get_by_name (G_TYPE_CHECK_INSTANCE_TYPE (source, gst_bin_get_type ()) ? ((GstBin*) source) : NULL, "fake");

```

